title: Jarrett Subloo
text:
Jarrett Subloo (born 29 July 2000) is an <a href="Australians">Australian</a> professional <a href="rugby%20league">rugby league</a> footballer who plays as a for the <a href="Canberra%20Raiders">Canberra Raiders</a> in the <a href="National%20Rugby%20League">National Rugby League</a> (NRL).
Background.
Born in <a href="Innisfail%2C%20Queensland">Innisfail, Queensland</a> and of <a href="Italian%20people">Italian</a> descent, Subloo played his junior rugby league for the Innisfail Leprechauns and attended <a href="Good%20Counsel%20College%2C%20Innisfail">Good Counsel College, Innisfail</a> before being signed by the <a href="Brisbane%20Broncos">Brisbane Broncos</a>. He later attended <a href="St%20Joseph%27s%20College%2C%20Nudgee">St Joseph's College, Nudgee</a> until he graduated in 2018.
Playing career.
Early career.
In 2016, Subloo played for the <a href="Norths%20Devils">Norths Devils</a> in the <a href="Cyril%20Connell%20Cup">Cyril Connell Cup</a>. In 2018, Subloo joined the <a href="Canberra%20Raiders">Canberra Raiders</a> and played for their <a href="SG%20Ball%20Cup">SG Ball Cup</a> side. In 2019, he moved up to the Raiders' <a href="Jersey%20Flegg%20Cup">Jersey Flegg Cup</a> side. On 4 October 2019, he was named in <a href="Italy%20national%20rugby%20league%20team">Italy</a>'s <a href="2021%20Rugby%20League%20World%20Cup%20qualifying">2021 Rugby League World Cup qualifying</a> squad but did not play a game. 
In November 2019, Subloo joined the Raiders' NRL squad as a development player.
2020.
In round 20 of the <a href="2020%20NRL%20season">2020 NRL season</a>, Subloo made his first grade debut for Canberra against the <a href="Cronulla-Sutherland%20Sharks">Cronulla-Sutherland Sharks</a> at Kogarah Oval coming onto the field with only one minute remaining.
Subloo made no further appearances for Canberra in the <a href="2020%20NRL%20season">2020 NRL season</a> as the club reached the preliminary final but were defeated by eventual premiers Melbourne 30-10.
